{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858765427,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e4a53001HsvWrwawSxu321","messageID":"msg_d796e2e30001XwzA5bZJpP6rkD","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1204ba178cf441358d9f0d01","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n208: \n209: ```python\n210: class DockerService:\n211:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n212:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n213:     def build_image(\n214:         self,\n215:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n216:         context_path: Path,\n217:         image_name: str,\n218:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n219:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n220:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n221:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n222:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n223:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n224:     def push_image(\n225:         self,\n226:         image_name: str,\n227:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n228:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n229:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n230:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n231:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n232:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n233:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: class MetadataService:\n240:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n241:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n242:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n243:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n244:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n245:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n246:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n250: \n251: ```python\n252: class KubernetesProvider:\n253:     def __init__(\n254:         self,\n255:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n256:         verbose: bool = False,\n257:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n258:     ) -> None: ...\n259:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n260:     def deploy_agent(\n261:         self,\n262:         agent_name: str,\n263:         image_url: str,\n264:         port: int,\n265:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n266:         replicas: int = 1,\n267:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n268:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n269:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n270:     def _create_deployment(\n271:         self,\n272:         name: str,\n273:         image_url: str,\n274:         port: int,\n275:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n276:         replicas: int,\n277:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n278:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n279:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n280:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n281:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n282:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n283:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n287: \n288: ```python\n289: class AgentCubeProvider:\n290:     def __init__(\n291:         self,\n292:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n293:         verbose: bool = False,\n294:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n295:     ) -> None: ...\n296:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n297:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n298:         self,\n299:         agent_name: str,\n300:         image_url: str,\n301:         port: int,\n302:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n303:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n304:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n306:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n307:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n308:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n309:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n310:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n311: ```\n312: \n313: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n314: \n315: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n316: \n317: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n318: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n319: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n320: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n321: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n322: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n323: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n324: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n325: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n326: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n327: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n328: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n329: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n330: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n331: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n332: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n333: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n334: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n335: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n336: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n337: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n338: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n339: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n340: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n341: \n342: Validators: `validate_language` → `['python','java']` lowercase; `validate_build_mode` → `['local','cloud']` lowercase; `validate_port` → `1..65535`.\n343: \n344: ## `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n345: \n346: Dataclass fields (all `Optional` unless noted):\n347: \n348: | Field | Type | Default |\n349: |-------|------|---------|\n350: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n351: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n352: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n353: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n354: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n355: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n356: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n357: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n358: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n359: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n360: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n361: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n362: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n363: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n364: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n365: \n366: ```python\n367: @classmethod\n368: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n372: \n373: **`[project]` dependencies:**\n374: \n375: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`\n376: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`\n377: - `pyyaml>=6.0`\n378: - `httpx>=0.24.0`\n379: - `docker>=6.0.0`\n380: - `rich>=13.0.0`\n381: - `packaging>=23.0`\n382: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0`\n383: - `semver>=3.0.0`\n384: \n385: **Optional `[project.optional-dependencies]`:**\n386: \n387: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n388: - `dev`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `ruff>=0.1.0`, `mypy>=1.5.0`, `pre-commit>=3.3.0`, `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n389: - `test`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`, `httpx-mock>=0.10.0`\n390: \n391: **Python:** `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`.\n392: \n393: ## Top-level exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n394: \n395: - `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n396: - `__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"`\n397: - `__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"`\n398: - Imports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n399: - `__all__` = `[\"app\", \"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\"]`  \n400:   (`StatusRuntime` is not exported here.)\n\n(End of file - total 400 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n\n## Package layout (every module path and role)\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775858765418,"end":1775858765425}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858766760,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e4f3e001vebVWO1IXrE7zh","messageID":"msg_d796e2e30001XwzA5bZJpP6rkD","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9f12285d5c024695be5b2d7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n10: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Version display\n13: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n14: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n15: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n18: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n19: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n20: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n21: \n22: ### Requirement: `pack` command\n23: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n26: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n27: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n28: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Successful pack\n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n36: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n37: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `build` command\n41: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n44: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n45: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n46: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n49: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n50: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n51: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Version increment on build\n54: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n55: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n56: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: `publish` command\n59: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n62: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n63: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n66: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n67: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n68: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n71: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n72: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n76: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n79: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n80: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Invalid payload\n83: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n84: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n85: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Invalid header format\n88: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n89: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n90: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n93: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n94: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n95: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: `status` command\n98: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n101: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n102: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Not published\n105: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n106: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n107: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n110: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Missing workspace\n113: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n115: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n118: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n119: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n123: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Save location\n126: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n127: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n128: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Schema validation\n131: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n132: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n133: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker integration\n136: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n140: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Push image\n144: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n145: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Remove image\n149: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n150: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n154: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Deploy agent\n157: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n158: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n159: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Wait for ready\n162: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n163: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Delete agent\n167: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n168: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Deploy CR\n175: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n176: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n180: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n183: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n184: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n185: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n188: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n191: - **GIVEN** a subcommand’s local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n192: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n193: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand’s `verbose` flag\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: **Note:** The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nCommand-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Global CLI options\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n\n#### Scenario: Version display\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md","time":{"start":1775858766751,"end":1775858766757}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775858766781,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e53a7001XwGxIrztz2gUdx","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d796e2e30001XwzA5bZJpP6rkD","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22518,"input":22058,"output":360,"reasoning":100,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.006847468}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775858772037,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e6843001Kycc7coqb08K62","messageID":"msg_d796e53da001rw9PiqujrmXVQT","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858773753,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e6a770012xNmfPYc2XwEn4","messageID":"msg_d796e53da001rw9PiqujrmXVQT","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a8aaf15067034469a65132dd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) 是 AgentCube CLI 的 Docker 守护进程交互层，封装 `docker` SDK for Python（`docker>=6.0.0`），提供镜像构建、推送、登录、打标、信息查询和清理能力。它被 `BuildRuntime`（本地 Docker 构建）和 `PublishRuntime`（本地镜像推送至 Registry）直接调用。\n6: \n7: **Scope**: 补全 spec 中定义但当前实现缺失的方法（`get_image_info`、`_get_image_info`、`remove_image`），修正与 spec 不一致的签名（`push_image`、`_docker_login_sdk`、`_tag_image_sdk` 的返回值类型），并完善错误处理。\n8: \n9: **Size**: M — 约 60 行新增代码 + 签名调整 + 测试覆盖。\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## Architecture\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                     CLI Commands                         │\n18: │  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status               │\n19: └──────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────┘\n20:            │                          │\n21:     ┌──────▼──────┐            ┌──────▼──────┐\n22:     │BuildRuntime │            │PublishRuntime│\n23:     └──────┬──────┘            └──────┬──────┘\n24:            │                          │\n25:            │  check_docker_available()│\n26:            │  build_image()           │  check_docker_available()\n27:            │                          │  _docker_login_sdk()\n28:            │                          │  push_image()\n29:            └──────────┬───────────────┘\n30:                       │\n31:               ┌───────▼───────┐\n32:               │ DockerService │\n33:               │               │\n34:               │ docker.from_  │\n35:               │    env()      │\n36:               └───────┬───────┘\n37:                       │\n38:               ┌───────▼───────┐\n39:               │  Docker SDK   │\n40:               │  (docker-py)  │\n41:               └───────────────┘\n42: ```\n43: \n44: **Design principles**:\n45: - 每次方法调用独立创建 `docker.from_env()` 客户端（无状态、线程安全、避免长连接泄漏）\n46: - 所有公共方法返回 `Dict[str, Any]` 或 `bool`，异常向上传播由 Runtime 层捕获\n47: - `_` 前缀方法为内部辅助，不供外部直接调用\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Component Design\n52: \n53: ### `DockerService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n54: \n55: 存储 `verbose` 标志，用于后续可选的详细日志输出（当前实现中 verbose 未主动使用，保留接口以匹配其他 Service 的一致性）。\n56: \n57: ### `check_docker_available() -> bool`\n58: \n59: 通过 `docker.from_env()` 创建客户端并调用 `client.ping()`。任何异常（连接失败、权限不足、守护进程未运行）返回 `False`。\n60: \n61: **Current**: ✅ 已实现，符合 spec。\n62: \n63: ### `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args) -> Dict[str, str]`\n64: \n65: 调用 `client.images.build()` 执行构建，返回包含 `image_name`、`image_id`（short_id）、`image_size`（人类可读格式）、`build_time`（秒数，保留两位小数）的字典。\n66: \n67: `build_args` 用于传递代理设置（如 `HTTP_PROXY`/`HTTPS_PROXY`），直接透传给 Docker SDK 的 `buildargs` 参数。\n68: \n69: **Current**: ✅ 已实现，符合 spec。\n70: \n71: ### `get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n72: \n73: 获取本地镜像的元信息。公共方法，内部委托给 `_get_image_info`。\n74: \n75: 返回字典包含：\n76: - `image_id`: 完整 SHA256 ID\n77: - `short_id`: 截短的 ID（`sha256:xxxxx`）\n78: - `size`: 人类可读大小（如 `50.0 MB`）\n79: - `tags`: 镜像关联的标签列表\n80: - `created`: 创建时间字符串\n81: \n82: **Current**: ❌ 缺失，需新增。\n83: \n84: ### `_get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n85: \n86: 内部实现：通过 `client.images.get(image_name)` 获取 `Image` 对象，从 `attrs` 中提取元数据并格式化。\n87: \n88: **Current**: ❌ 缺失，需新增。\n89: \n90: ### `_format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str`\n91: \n92: 将字节数格式化为人类可读字符串。阈值：`<1024` → `B`，`<1MB` → `KB`，`<1GB` → `MB`，`>=1GB` → `GB`。\n93: \n94: **Current**: ✅ 已实现，符合 spec。\n95: \n96: ### `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password) -> Dict[str, str]`\n97: \n98: 将本地镜像推送至 Registry。\n99: \n100: **Spec 签名**（与当前实现不同）:\n101: ```python\n102: def push_image(\n103:     self,\n104:     image_name: str,\n105:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n107:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n108: ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **当前签名**:\n112: ```python\n113: def push_image(\n114:     self,\n115:     image_tag: str,          # 完整标签如 registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\n116:     registry_url: str,       # 必填\n117:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n118:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n119: ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **需要调整**: 将 `push_image` 签名改为 spec 定义的 `image_name` + 可选 `registry_url`，内部逻辑：\n123: 1. 如果提供 `registry_url`，先调用 `_tag_image_sdk` 将 `image_name` 打目标标签\n124: 2. 如果提供 `username` 和 `password`，调用 `_docker_login_sdk` 登录\n125: 3. 调用 `client.images.push()` 推送，流式处理日志（当前未消费 push 返回值中的流式日志）\n126: 4. 返回 `{\"pushed_image\": <full_tag>, \"push_time\": \"<n.nn>s\"}`（spec 要求返回 `pushed_image` 和 `push_time`）\n127: \n128: **Current**: ⚠️ 已实现但签名与 spec 不一致，返回值缺少 `push_time`。\n129: \n130: ### `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password) -> None`\n131: \n132: 通过 `client.login()` 登录 Registry。\n133: \n134: **Spec 返回值**: `None`\n135: **当前返回值**: `bool`（返回 `True`）\n136: \n137: **需要调整**: 返回值改为 `None`，失败时让 `docker.errors.APIError` 向上传播。\n138: \n139: **Current**: ⚠️ 已实现但返回值类型与 spec 不一致。\n140: \n141: ### `_tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image) -> None`\n142: \n143: 将本地镜像从 `source_image` 打标为 `target_image`。\n144: \n145: **Spec 返回值**: `None`\n146: **当前返回值**: `bool`（返回 `True`）\n147: \n148: **需要调整**: 返回值改为 `None`。\n149: \n150: **Current**: ⚠️ 已实现但返回值类型与 spec 不一致。\n151: \n152: ### `remove_image(image_name: str) -> bool`\n153: \n154: 删除本地 Docker 镜像。成功返回 `True`；失败时记录 warning 日志并返回 `False`。\n155: \n156: 使用 `client.images.remove(image_name)` 执行删除。捕获 `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` 和 `docker.errors.APIError`，记录 warning 后返回 `False`。\n157: \n158: **Current**: ❌ 缺失，需新增。\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## Data Flow Details\n163: \n164: ### Build 流程\n165: \n166: ```\n167: BuildRuntime._build_local()\n168:   ├── DockerService.check_docker_available()  → bool\n169:   └── DockerService.build_image()\n170:         ├── docker.from_env()\n171:         ├── client.images.build(path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs)\n172:         ├── client.images.get(image.id)       → 获取 Size\n173:         └── return {image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time}\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ### Publish 流程（local build mode）\n177: \n178: ```\n179: PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()\n180:   ├── DockerService.check_docker_available()  → bool\n181:   ├── DockerService._docker_login_sdk()       → None (if credentials)\n182:   └── DockerService.push_image()\n183:         ├── docker.from_env()\n184:         ├── client.images.push(repository, tag, auth_config)\n185:         └── return {pushed_image, push_time}\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## Error Handling\n191: \n192: | 场景 | 异常类型 | 处理方式 |\n193: |------|----------|----------|\n194: | Docker 守护进程不可达 | `docker.errors.DockerException` | `check_docker_available()` 返回 `False`；其他方法向上传播 |\n195: | 镜像不存在 | `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | `remove_image()` 返回 `False` + warning；其他方法向上传播 |\n196: | 构建失败 | `docker.errors.BuildError` | 向上传播，由 `BuildRuntime` / CLI `_handle_error` 捕获 |\n197: | Registry 认证失败 | `docker.errors.APIError` | `_docker_login_sdk()` 向上传播；`push_image()` 向上传播 |\n198: | 推送失败 | `docker.errors.APIError` | 向上传播，由 `PublishRuntime` / CLI 捕获 |\n199: | 权限不足 | `docker.errors.APIError` (403) | 向上传播 |\n200: \n201: **关键约束**: `DockerService` 本身不打印错误信息或调用 `sys.exit()` — 所有异常向上传播，由 Runtime 层或 CLI `_handle_error` 统一处理。\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Testing Strategy\n206: \n207: ### 现有测试覆盖（`tests/services/test_docker_service.py`）\n208: \n209: | 测试类 | 覆盖方法 | 状态 |\n210: |--------|----------|------|\n211: | `TestDockerServiceCheckDockerAvailableRunning` | `check_docker_available` (success) | ✅ |\n212: | `TestDockerServiceCheckDockerAvailableNotRunning` | `check_docker_available` (failure) | ✅ |\n213: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageSuccess` | `build_image` (success) | ✅ |\n214: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageWithProxy` | `build_image` (with buildargs) | ✅ |\n215: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageFailure` | `build_image` (error propagation) | ✅ |\n216: | `TestDockerServiceFormatSize*` | `_format_size` (B/KB/MB/GB) | ✅ |\n217: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_Success` | `push_image` (success) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n218: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_WithCredentials` | `push_image` (auth) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n219: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_Failure` | `push_image` (APIError) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n220: | `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success` | `_docker_login_sdk` (success) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n221: | `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Failure` | `_docker_login_sdk` (APIError) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n222: | `TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success` | `_tag_image_sdk` (success) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n223: \n224: ### 需新增测试\n225: \n226: | 测试类 | 覆盖方法 | 场景 |\n227: |--------|----------|------|\n228: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `get_image_info` | 存在镜像，返回完整元信息 |\n229: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `get_image_info` | 镜像不存在，抛出 `ImageNotFound` |\n230: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `_get_image_info` | 内部实现验证 |\n231: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | 成功删除返回 `True` |\n232: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | 镜像不存在返回 `False` + warning |\n233: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | API 错误返回 `False` + warning |\n234: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | 新签名：`image_name` + `registry_url` |\n235: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | 无 `registry_url` 时直接推送本地标签 |\n236: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | 返回 `push_time` |\n237: \n238: ### Mock 策略\n239: \n240: 所有测试通过 `patch(\"agentcube.services.docker_service.docker.from_env\")` 模拟 Docker 客户端，不依赖真实 Docker 守护进程。\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Implementation Notes\n245: \n246: ### 签名变更影响分析\n247: \n248: `push_image` 签名变更会影响以下调用方：\n249: \n250: 1. **`PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()`** (`publish_runtime.py:105`):\n251:    ```python\n252:    # Before:\n253:    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url or \"\", username, password)\n254:    # After:\n255:    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url or \"\", username, password)\n256:    ```\n257:    调用方传递的第一个参数是完整 `image_tag`（如 `registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0`），在新签名中作为 `image_name` 使用。如果 `registry_url` 为空字符串，不进行重新打标，直接推送。行为兼容。\n258: \n259: 2. **测试文件** (`test_docker_service.py`): 需更新断言以匹配新返回值（`push_time` 替代 `status`）。\n260: \n261: ### 返回值类型变更\n262: \n263: `_docker_login_sdk` 和 `_tag_image_sdk` 的返回值从 `bool` 改为 `None`。由于它们是 `_` 前缀的内部方法，且调用方不检查返回值（`publish_runtime.py:103` 调用 `_docker_login_sdk` 但未使用返回值），此变更为安全。\n264: \n265: ### 缺失方法实现要点\n266: \n267: **`get_image_info` / `_get_image_info`**:\n268: ```python\n269: def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n270:     client = docker.from_env()\n271:     image = client.images.get(image_name)\n272:     attrs = image.attrs\n273:     return {\n274:         \"image_id\": image.id,\n275:         \"short_id\": image.short_id,\n276:         \"size\": self._format_size(int(attrs.get(\"Size\", 0) or 0)),\n277:         \"tags\": \", \".join(image.tags) if image.tags else \"<none>\",\n278:         \"created\": attrs.get(\"Created\", \"unknown\"),\n279:     }\n280: \n281: def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n282:     return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n283: ```\n284: \n285: **`remove_image`**:\n286: ```python\n287: def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n288:     import logging\n289:     logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n290:     try:\n291:         client = docker.from_env()\n292:         client.images.remove(image_name)\n293:         return True\n294:     except (docker.errors.ImageNotFound, docker.errors.APIError) as e:\n295:         logger.warning(\"Failed to remove image %s: %s\", image_name, e)\n296:         return False\n297: ```\n298: \n299: **`push_image` 签名调整**:\n300: ```python\n301: def push_image(\n302:     self,\n303:     image_name: str,\n304:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n306:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n307: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n308:     import time\n309:     client = docker.from_env()\n310:     start_time = time.time()\n311: \n312:     if registry_url:\n313:         # Determine target tag\n314:         parts = image_name.rsplit(\":\", 1)\n315:         repo = parts[0]\n316:         tag = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"latest\"\n317:         target = f\"{registry_url}/{repo}:{tag}\"\n318:         self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target)\n319:         push_repo = f\"{registry_url}/{repo}\"\n320:         push_tag = tag\n321:     else:\n322:         parts = image_name.rsplit(\":\", 1)\n323:         push_repo = parts[0]\n324:         push_tag = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"latest\"\n325: \n326:     auth_config = None\n327:     if username and password:\n328:         auth_config = {\"username\": username, \"password\": password}\n329:         self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n330: \n331:     client.images.push(push_repo, tag=push_tag, auth_config=auth_config)\n332:     push_time = time.time() - start_time\n333:     return {\"pushed_image\": image_name, \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\"}\n334: ```\n\n(End of file - total 334 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\n`DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) 是 AgentCube CLI 的 Docker 守护进程交互层，封装 `docker` SDK for Python（`docker>=6.0.0`），提供镜像构建、推送、登录、打标、信息查询和清理能力。它被 `BuildRuntime`（本地 Docker 构建）和 `PublishRuntime`（本地镜像推送至 Registry）直接调用。\n\n**Scope**: 补全 spec 中定义但当前实现缺失的方法（`get_image_info`、`_get_image_info`、`remove_image`），修正与 spec 不一致的签名（`push_image`、`_docker_login_sdk`、`_tag_image_sdk` 的返回值类型），并完善错误处理。\n\n**Size**: M — 约 60 行新增代码 + 签名调整 + 测试覆盖。\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     CLI Commands                         │\n│  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status               │\n└──────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────┘\n           │                          │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775858773744,"end":1775858773751}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858775102,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e6f7f0014TJ7GC95rQYq4p","messageID":"msg_d796e53da001rw9PiqujrmXVQT","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9ea6be742f7f4ebbab14ed27","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: DockerService initialization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that encapsulates Docker SDK operations, initialized with an optional `verbose` flag.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Default initialization\n17: - **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called with no arguments\n18: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n19: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `False` and a Docker client SHALL be initialized via `docker.from_env()`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Verbose initialization\n22: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)` is called\n23: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n24: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `True` and the logger SHALL be configured for debug-level output\n25: \n26: ### Requirement: Docker availability check\n27: \n28: The system SHALL verify that the Docker daemon is running and reachable before attempting build or push operations.\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Docker is available\n31: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is running and accessible\n32: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Docker is unavailable\n36: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is not running or the SDK cannot connect\n37: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL catch `docker.errors.DockerException` (or connection errors) and return `False`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Build image\n41: \n42: The system SHALL build a Docker image from a Dockerfile and context path, with optional build arguments and a configurable tag.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Build with default tag\n45: - **GIVEN** a valid `dockerfile_path` and `context_path`\n46: - **WHEN** `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, \"my-agent\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** it SHALL build the image tagged `my-agent:latest` and return a dict with keys `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Build with custom tag\n50: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace\n51: - **WHEN** `build_image(..., image_name=\"my-agent\", tag=\"v1.2.3\")` is called\n52: - **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged `my-agent:v1.2.3`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Build with build arguments\n55: - **GIVEN** `build_args={\"PIP_INDEX_URL\": \"https://proxy.example.com/simple\"}` is passed\n56: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n57: - **THEN** the Docker build SHALL receive `buildargs` containing the provided key-value pairs\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Build failure\n60: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile contains a syntax error or a build step fails\n61: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with a message describing the build failure\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Build records elapsed time\n65: - **GIVEN** a build is initiated\n66: - **WHEN** `build_image` completes successfully\n67: - **THEN** the returned dict SHALL include `build_time` as a formatted duration string (e.g., `\"12.34s\"`)\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Image info retrieval\n70: \n71: The system SHALL retrieve metadata about a local Docker image, including its ID and human-readable size.\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Image exists locally\n74: - **GIVEN** an image `my-agent:latest` exists in the local Docker daemon\n75: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"my-agent:latest\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL return a dict with keys `image_id` and `image_size` (human-readable, e.g., `\"256.5 MB\"`)\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Image does not exist\n79: - **GIVEN** no image named `nonexistent:latest` exists locally\n80: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the image was not found\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: Size formatting\n84: \n85: The system SHALL convert byte counts to human-readable size strings.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Bytes\n88: - **GIVEN** a size of `512` bytes\n89: - **WHEN** `_format_size(512)` is called\n90: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"512 B\"`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Megabytes\n93: - **GIVEN** a size of `1048576` bytes (1 MiB)\n94: - **WHEN** `_format_size(1048576)` is called\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"1.0 MB\"`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Gigabytes\n98: - **GIVEN** a size of `1073741824` bytes (1 GiB)\n99: - **WHEN** `_format_size(1073741824)` is called\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"1.0 GB\"`\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Push image\n103: \n104: The system SHALL push a local Docker image to a registry, optionally authenticating and retagging.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Push without registry URL\n107: - **GIVEN** a local image `my-agent:v1.0.0` exists\n108: - **WHEN** `push_image(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\")` is called with no `registry_url`\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL push the image to its existing tag and return a dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Push with registry URL and credentials\n112: - **GIVEN** `registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"`, `username`, and `password` are provided\n113: - **WHEN** `push_image(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\", registry_url, username, password)` is called\n114: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n115:   1. Login to the registry via `_docker_login_sdk`\n116:   2. Retag the image to `{registry_url}/my-agent:v1.0.0` via `_tag_image_sdk`\n117:   3. Push the retagged image\n118:   4. Return `pushed_image` as the full registry-prefixed tag\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Push without credentials\n121: - **GIVEN** `registry_url` is provided but `username` or `password` is `None`\n122: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL skip the login step and attempt to push using existing Docker credentials\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Push failure\n126: - **GIVEN** the registry is unreachable or authentication fails\n127: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with a message describing the push failure\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Push records elapsed time\n131: - **GIVEN** a push is initiated\n132: - **WHEN** `push_image` completes successfully\n133: - **THEN** the returned dict SHALL include `push_time` as a formatted duration string\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker login\n136: \n137: The system SHALL authenticate to a Docker registry using the Docker SDK.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Successful login\n140: - **GIVEN** valid `registry`, `username`, and `password`\n141: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` is called\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL call `client.login()` with the provided credentials and succeed without raising\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Login failure\n145: - **GIVEN** invalid credentials or unreachable registry\n146: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk` is called\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with the login error message\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: Image tagging\n150: \n151: The system SHALL retag a local Docker image.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Successful tag\n154: - **GIVEN** source image `my-agent:v1.0.0` exists\n155: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\", \"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\")` is called\n156: - **THEN** the target tag SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Tag failure\n159: - **GIVEN** the source image does not exist\n160: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk` is called\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with the tagging error message\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Remove image\n164: \n165: The system SHALL remove a local Docker image and handle failures gracefully.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Successful removal\n168: - **GIVEN** image `my-agent:old` exists locally\n169: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"my-agent:old\")` is called\n170: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True` and the image SHALL no longer be listed locally\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Removal failure\n173: - **GIVEN** image `my-agent:in-use` is referenced by a running container or does not exist\n174: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"my-agent:in-use\")` is called\n175: - **THEN** it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: Verbose logging during operations\n178: \n179: The system SHALL emit detailed logs during Docker operations when `verbose=True`.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Verbose build logging\n182: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)`\n183: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL log the Dockerfile path, context path, image name, tag, and any build arguments\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Verbose push logging\n187: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)`\n188: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called with credentials\n189: - **THEN** it SHALL log the registry URL, username (not password), and target image name\n190: \n191: ## File changes\n192: \n193: | Action | File | Description |\n194: |--------|------|-------------|\n195: | Add | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | DockerService class with build, push, info, remove operations |\n196: | Add | `tests/services/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: DockerService initialization\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that encapsulates Docker SDK operations, initialized with an optional `verbose` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Default initialization\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `False` and a Docker client SHALL be initialized via `docker.from_env()`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775858775094,"end":1775858775100}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858776470,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e74c4001Z2fAJiipXvWL2N","messageID":"msg_d796e53da001rw9PiqujrmXVQT","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f3acfb54b807427b85cb9ac7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: **Language:** Python\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## 目的\n8: \n9: \n10: \n11: ## 范围\n12: \n13: ### 包含\n14: \n15: \n16: \n17: ### 不包含\n18: \n19: \n20: \n21: ## 架构概要\n22: \n23: \n24: \n25: ## 上游依赖\n26: \n27: \n28: \n29: ## 状态\n30: \n31: - [ ] 提案审查\n32: - [ ] 实现\n33: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 33 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## 目的\n\n\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n\n\n\n### 不包含\n\n\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858776463,"end":1775858776469}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858777774,"sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","part":{"id":"prt_d796e7a1b001x0Dte0BMx1P2q7","messageID":"msg_d796e53da001rw9PiqujrmXVQT","sessionID":"ses_28694e834ffeTByYEeRz1cyhMq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f2f05500387845d69b3937d8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-024/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-024/design.md`, `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** None\n9: \n10: ## T1. Fix `_docker_login_sdk` return type: `bool` → `None`\n11: \n12: - [ ] Change `_docker_login_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n13: - [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `client.login()` result fall through\n14: - [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n15: - [ ] Write test: successful login returns `None` (no exception raised)\n16: - [ ] Write test: login failure raises `docker.errors.APIError` (propagates upward)\n17: \n18: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## T2. Fix `_tag_image_sdk` return type: `bool` → `None`\n23: \n24: - [ ] Change `_tag_image_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n25: - [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `image.tag()` result fall through\n26: - [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n27: - [ ] Write test: successful tagging returns `None` (no exception raised)\n28: - [ ] Write test: tagging failure (source image not found) raises `docker.errors.ImageNotFound`\n29: \n30: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## T3. Implement `_get_image_info` (internal helper)\n35: \n36: - [ ] Add `_get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` method\n37: - [ ] Create `docker.from_env()` client inside method\n38: - [ ] Call `client.images.get(image_name)` to retrieve `Image` object\n39: - [ ] Extract `image_id` (full ID), `short_id`, `size` (via `_format_size`), `tags` (comma-joined or `\"<none>\"`), `created` from `image.attrs`\n40: - [ ] Return dict with keys: `image_id`, `short_id`, `size`, `tags`, `created`\n41: - [ ] Write test: image exists → returns dict with all five keys populated correctly\n42: - [ ] Write test: image not found → `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` propagates upward\n43: \n44: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` passes\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## T4. Implement `get_image_info` (public method)\n49: \n50: - [ ] Add `get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` method\n51: - [ ] Delegate to `self._get_image_info(image_name)`\n52: - [ ] Write test: delegates to `_get_image_info` and returns result\n53: - [ ] Write test: image not found → `ValueError` with descriptive message (per delta-spec)\n54: \n55: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` passes; public method wraps internal correctly\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## T5. Implement `remove_image`\n60: \n61: - [ ] Add `remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool` method\n62: - [ ] Create `docker.from_env()` client inside method\n63: - [ ] Call `client.images.remove(image_name)`; return `True` on success\n64: - [ ] Catch `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` → log warning, return `False`\n65: - [ ] Catch `docker.errors.APIError` → log warning, return `False`\n66: - [ ] Write test: image exists → returns `True`, `client.images.remove` called once\n67: - [ ] Write test: image not found → returns `False`, warning logged\n68: - [ ] Write test: API error (e.g., image in use) → returns `False`, warning logged\n69: \n70: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceRemoveImage -v` passes\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## T6. Fix `push_image` signature and implementation\n75: \n76: - [ ] Change first parameter from `image_tag: str` to `image_name: str`\n77: - [ ] Change `registry_url: str` to `registry_url: Optional[str] = None`\n78: - [ ] Add `import time` (if not already present at top of method)\n79: - [ ] Record `start_time = time.time()` at method entry\n80: - [ ] If `registry_url` is provided:\n81:   - Parse `image_name` to extract repo and tag\n82:   - Build target tag: `{registry_url}/{repo}:{tag}`\n83:   - Call `self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target)`\n84:   - Set `push_repo` and `push_tag` from target\n85: - [ ] If `registry_url` is not provided:\n86:   - Parse `image_name` to extract repo and tag\n87:   - Set `push_repo` and `push_tag` directly\n88: - [ ] If `username` and `password` provided, call `self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)`\n89: - [ ] Call `client.images.push(push_repo, tag=push_tag, auth_config=...)`\n90: - [ ] Compute `push_time = time.time() - start_time`\n91: - [ ] Return `{\"pushed_image\": image_name, \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\"}`\n92: - [ ] Update docstring to match new signature and return value\n93: - [ ] Write test: push without `registry_url` → pushes directly, returns `pushed_image` + `push_time`\n94: - [ ] Write test: push with `registry_url` and credentials → tags, logs in, pushes, returns full tag\n95: - [ ] Write test: push with `registry_url` but no credentials → skips login, pushes\n96: - [ ] Write test: push failure → `docker.errors.APIError` propagates upward\n97: \n98: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServicePushImageSpec -v` passes\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## T7. Update `PublishRuntime` caller for new `push_image` signature\n103: \n104: - [ ] Read `publish_runtime.py` to identify `push_image` call site(s)\n105: - [ ] Update call to match new signature: `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)`\n106: - [ ] Verify caller does not depend on old return keys (`status` → now `push_time`)\n107: - [ ] Write test: `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` works with new `push_image` signature (mocked `DockerService`)\n108: \n109: **Verification:** `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` passes; no `TypeError` from signature mismatch\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## T8. Update existing tests for signature/return changes\n114: \n115: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_Success` assertions: expect `push_time` key instead of `status`\n116: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_WithCredentials` assertions: match new signature and return\n117: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_Failure` assertions: verify `APIError` propagation\n118: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success` assertion: expect `None` return instead of `True`\n119: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Failure` assertion: verify `APIError` propagation\n120: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success` assertion: expect `None` return instead of `True`\n121: \n122: **Verification:** All existing `test_docker_service.py` tests pass with updated assertions\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## T9. Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n127: \n128: - [ ] `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — no violations\n129: - [ ] `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` — no violations\n130: - [ ] `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` — no type errors\n131: - [ ] `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py -v` — all pass\n132: - [ ] `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` — all pass\n133: - [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 90%\n134: \n135: **Verification:** All lint/type-check/test commands pass with zero errors\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Task Dependencies\n140: \n141: ```\n142: T1 ──┐\n143: T2 ──┼── T6 ── T7 ── T9\n144:      │           │\n145: T3 ──┤           │\n146: T4 ──┤           │\n147: T5 ──┤           │\n148:      │           │\n149: T8 ──┴───────────┘\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ## Parallelizable Groups\n153: \n154: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n155: |-------|-------|---------------|\n156: | G1 | T1, T2, T3, T5 | None (independent method changes) |\n157: | G2 | T4 | T3 |\n158: | G3 | T6 | T1, T2 |\n159: | G4 | T7, T8 | T6 |\n160: | G5 | T9 | T4, T5, T7, T8 |\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Acceptance Criteria\n165: \n166: | # | Criterion | Command |\n167: |---|-----------|---------|\n168: | AC1 | `get_image_info` returns dict with `image_id`, `short_id`, `size`, `tags`, `created` | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` |\n169: | AC2 | `remove_image` returns `True` on success, `False` + warning on failure | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServiceRemoveImage -v` |\n170: | AC3 | `push_image` accepts `image_name` + optional `registry_url`, returns `pushed_image` + `push_time` | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServicePushImageSpec -v` |\n171: | AC4 | `_docker_login_sdk` returns `None` (not `bool`) | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` |\n172: | AC5 | `_tag_image_sdk` returns `None` (not `bool`) | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success -v` |\n173: | AC6 | `PublishRuntime` caller updated and functional | `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` |\n174: | AC7 | All existing tests pass with updated assertions | `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n175: | AC8 | Lint and type-check pass | `ruff check` + `mypy` with zero violations |\n176: | AC9 | Test coverage ≥ 90% for `docker_service.py` | `pytest --cov=agentcube.services.docker_se